The paper deals with the geometric properties of tree drawings, specifically the partitioning of the plane into convex polygons and the optimization of angular resolution. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under computational geometry (cs.CG) or graph drawing (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms for solving the problem efficiently, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses strategies for setting edge lengths, which could be relevant to scientific computing (cs.SI).
